{"title_page": "Serhiy Sukhobok", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Serhiy Sukhobok\n| image         =\n| alt           = \n| caption       =\n| native_name      = \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u0439 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043b\u0456\u0439\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0431\u043e\u043a\n| native_name_lang = uk\n| birth_date    = June 1964\n| birth_place   = [[Pavlodar]], [[Kazakh SSR]], Soviet Union\n| death_date    = {{death date and age|2015|04|13|1964|6|df=yes}}\n| death_place   = [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]]\n| citizenship   = Ukraine\n| nationality   = \n| other_names   = Sergei Sukhobok\n| occupation    = journalist\n| years_active  =\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works =\n}}\n'''Serhiy Anatoliyovich Sukhobok''' ({{lang-ua|\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u0439 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043b\u0456\u0439\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0431\u043e\u043a}}) was a Ukrainian journalist and entrepreneur. He founded the newspaper ''Viddzerkalennya'' and co-founded two online publications, ''ProUA'' and ''Obkom''.\n\nThe son of Ukrainians from [[Chernihiv]], Sukhobok was born in June 1964 in [[Pavlodar]], [[Kazakh SSR]], and studied at [[Donetsk National Technical University]].<ref name=Obkom150416/><ref name=TK150416/> He was critical of oligarchs, particularly [[Rinat Akhmetov]], and state officials.<ref name=AP150416/><ref name=Unian150416/> Sukhobok was killed on 13 April 2015 on a [[dacha]] near Kiev, during a dispute that turned violent.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Pro-Russian journalist gunned down in Ukraine's capital|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/huff-wires/20150416/eu-ukraine-journalist-killed/?ir=world|accessdate = 2015-12-31}}</ref><ref name=AP150416/>{{Dead link|date=December 2015}}<ref>http://www.mvs.gov.ua/mvs/control/main/uk/publish/article/1446352{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=Obkom150416>{{cite news |url= http://obkom.net.ua/articles/2015-04/16.1214.shtml |title= \u041e \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0435 \u0421\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0431\u043e\u043a\u0435 |language= Russian |trans-title= About Serhiy Sukhobok |first= Alexei |last= Mironov |work= obkom.net.ua |date= 16 April 2015 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=TK150416>{{cite news |url= http://www.telekritika.ua/profesija/2015-04-16/106121 |title= \u0416\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u044f \u0421\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0431\u043e\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u043e-\u0437\u0432\u0456\u0440\u044f\u0447\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u0432\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u041a\u0438\u0454\u0432\u0456. \u041f\u0440\u043e\u0449\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u2013 17 \u043a\u0432\u0456\u0442\u043d\u044f |language= Ukrainian |trans-title= Journalist Serhiy Sukhobok killed in Kyiv |work= telekritika.ua |date= 16 April 2015 |access-date= 17 April 2015 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150417184214/http://www.telekritika.ua/profesija/2015-04-16/106121 |archive-date= 17 April 2015 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=AP150416>{{cite news |url= http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/E/EU_UKRAINE_JOURNALIST_KILLED?SITE=AP&SECTION=HOME&TEMPLATE=DEFAULT |title= Pro-Russian journalist gunned down in Ukraine's capital |first= Nataliya |last= Vasilyeva |work= [[Associated Press]] |date= 16 April 2015 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Unian150416>{{cite news |url= http://www.unian.info/society/1067807-journalist-serhiy-sukhobok-killed.html |title= Journalist Serhiy Sukhobok killed |work= unian.info |date= 16 April 2015 }}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sukhobok, Serhiy}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:2015 deaths]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian journalists]]\n[[Category:Journalists killed in Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Male journalists]]\n[[Category:Assassinated Ukrainian journalists]]\n\n\n{{Ukraine-journalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name          = Serhiy Sukhobok\n| image         =\n| alt           = \n| caption       =\n| native_name      = \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u0439 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043b\u0456\u0439\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0431\u043e\u043a\n| native_name_lang = uk\n| birth_date    = June 1964\n| birth_place   = [[Pavlodar]], [[Kazakh SSR]], Soviet Union\n| death_date    = {{death date and age|2015|04|13|1964|6|df=yes}}\n| death_place   = [[Kiev]], [[Ukraine]]\n| citizenship   = Ukraine\n| nationality   = \n| other_names   = Sergei Sukhobok\n| occupation    = journalist\n| years_active  =\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works =\n}}\n'''Serhiy Anatoliyovich Sukhobok''' ({{lang-ua|\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u0439 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u0442\u043e\u043b\u0456\u0439\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0421\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0431\u043e\u043a}}) was a Ukrainian journalist and entrepreneur. He founded the newspaper ''Viddzerkalennya'' and co-founded two online publications, ''ProUA'' and ''Obkom''.\n\nThe son of Ukrainians from [[Chernihiv]], Sukhobok was born in June 1964 in [[Pavlodar]], [[Kazakh SSR]], and studied at [[Donetsk National Technical University]].<ref name=Obkom150416/><ref name=TK150416/> He was critical of oligarchs, particularly [[Rinat Akhmetov]], and state officials.<ref name=AP150416/><ref name=Unian150416/> Sukhobok was killed on 13 April 2015 on a [[dacha]] near Kiev, during a dispute that turned violent.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Pro-Russian journalist gunned down in Ukraine's capital|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/huff-wires/20150416/eu-ukraine-journalist-killed/?ir=world|accessdate = 2015-12-31}}</ref><ref name=AP150416/>{{Dead link|date=December 2015}}<ref>http://www.mvs.gov.ua/mvs/control/main/uk/publish/article/1446352{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=Obkom150416>{{cite news |url= http://obkom.net.ua/articles/2015-04/16.1214.shtml |title= \u041e \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0435 \u0421\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0431\u043e\u043a\u0435 |language= Russian |trans-title= About Serhiy Sukhobok |first= Alexei |last= Mironov |work= obkom.net.ua |date= 16 April 2015 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=TK150416>{{cite news |url= http://www.telekritika.ua/profesija/2015-04-16/106121 |title= \u0416\u0443\u0440\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0456\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u044f \u0421\u0443\u0445\u043e\u0431\u043e\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u043e-\u0437\u0432\u0456\u0440\u044f\u0447\u043e\u043c\u0443 \u0432\u0431\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u041a\u0438\u0454\u0432\u0456. \u041f\u0440\u043e\u0449\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044f \u2013 17 \u043a\u0432\u0456\u0442\u043d\u044f |language= Ukrainian |trans-title= Journalist Serhiy Sukhobok killed in Kyiv |work= telekritika.ua |date= 16 April 2015 |access-date= 17 April 2015 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150417184214/http://www.telekritika.ua/profesija/2015-04-16/106121 |archive-date= 17 April 2015 |url-status= dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=AP150416>{{cite news |url= http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/E/EU_UKRAINE_JOURNALIST_KILLED?SITE=AP&SECTION=HOME&TEMPLATE=DEFAULT |title= Pro-Russian journalist gunned down in Ukraine's capital |first= Nataliya |last= Vasilyeva |work= [[Associated Press]] |date= 16 April 2015 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Unian150416>{{cite news |url= http://www.unian.info/society/1067807-journalist-serhiy-sukhobok-killed.html |title= Journalist Serhiy Sukhobok killed |work= unian.info |date= 16 April 2015 }}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sukhobok, Serhiy}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:2015 deaths]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian journalists]]\n[[Category:Journalists killed in Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Male journalists]]\n[[Category:Assassinated Ukrainian journalists]]\n\n{{Ukraine-journalist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serhiy_Sukhobok"}
